    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: PET Scan - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
    <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_pet_scan">PET Scan</xref>
 is a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_clinical_investigation">Clinical Investigation</xref>.        </p>
    <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_pet_scan">PET Scan</xref>
 (<xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_pet_scan">Positron Emission Tomography Scan</xref>) produces three-dimensional, colour images that show how 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_tissue">TISSUES</xref>
 work.        </p>
    <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_pet_scan">PET Scan</xref>
 can be used to diagnose a condition or to see how a condition is developing.        </p>
    <p>
For further information on 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_pet_scan">PET Scans</xref>, see the NHS website at: 
              <xref href="https://www.nhs.uk/conditions/pet-scan/" scope="external" format="html">PET scan</xref>.        </p>
  </div>
